ators in this app."><div class=3D"bARER" data-g-id=3D"description">Easily m=
aster the math involved in quilting! Robert Kaufman Fabrics and Quilters Pa=
radise have joined forces to bring you this updated collection of eight ess=
ential quilting calculators. Designed by quilters, the calculators work wit=
h both U.S. and metric measurements. With these tools you=E2=80=99ll easily=
 and accurately work out how many rectangular pieces can be cut from a larg=
er piece, or how much fabric is needed for backing, batting and borders, sq=
uare-in-a-square, set-in and corner triangles, and more.<br> <br>We=E2=80=
=99ve also added an AI chatbot to answer your questions and give advice on =
every aspect of quilting.<br> <br>Our calculators:<br> <br>=E2=80=A2 Fabric=
 Measurement Converter: Converts between measurement in decimals and fracti=
ons.<br><br>=E2=80=A2 Backing and Batting Calculator: Determines how much y=
ardage from a bolt of fabric is needed to make the backing for a quilt.<br>=
<br>=E2=80=A2 Piece Count Calculator: Shows the number of fixed-size pieces=
 that can be cut from a larger piece of fabric.<br><br>=E2=80=A2 Pieces to =
Yardage Calculator: Indicates how much fabric is needed in order to cut a g=
iven number of fixed-size pieces.<br><br>=E2=80=A2 Binding Calculator: Tell=
s you the amount of fabric required to bind your quilt, based on the quilt=
=E2=80=99s dimensions and the binding strip width.<br><br>=E2=80=A2 Border =
Calculator: Shows the amount of fabric required to create borders, based on=
 your quilt=E2=80=99s dimensions and the width of the borders.<br><br>=E2=
=80=A2 Square-in-a-Square Calculator: Works out the key dimensions of a squ=
are-in-a-square block.<br><br>=E2=80=A2 Set-in and Corner Triangle Calculat=
or: Determines the size of the square piece you=E2=80=99ll need to cut in o=
rder to create both unfinished set-in triangles and corner triangles.</div>=
